session:
  updated: 2026-07-18
  status: agentic_lifecycle_added
  branch: feature/agentic-lifecycle

goal:
  current: add a connected agentic development lifecycle (calibrate, ideate, spec, ATDD, review, wiki graph)

completed:
  - standing quality, technical-debt and right-sizing rules in AGENTS.md
  - boundary-in ATDD testing posture reconciled with the testing trophy
  - calibrate-audience discovery skill (skill level, app shape, recorded right-sizing)
  - audience section in PROJECT_PROFILE.toon and CUSTOMIZE_THIS_PROJECT.toon; check-project-profile enforces it
  - OpenSpec-shaped, TOON-encoded spec system (specs/capabilities, changes, archive)
  - change.toon and capability.toon templates and schemas
  - check-changes validator (stdlib TOON parser; deltas, scenarios, acceptance mapping, edge resolution)
  - ideate and narrative-intake skills; /ideate command
  - per-persona stance (discourages/accepts/encourages) in communication rules
  - outside-in-tdd skill and testing wiki
  - review-loop skill with per-language smell sections; /review command
  - wiki-tidy skill, TAXONOMY.md, warn-only check-wiki, opt-in install-hooks
  - lifecycle propagated into README, wiki and .agentic-template/templates
  - self-test extended with change-spec fixtures

in_progress: []

next:
  - open a PR for feature/agentic-lifecycle with test evidence
  - human or lead agent owns merge

decisions:
  - id: spec_openspec_shaped_toon_encoded
    summary: specs follow the OpenSpec model but are TOON-encoded and agent-first; markdown holds rationale only; no openspec CLI dependency
  - id: testing_boundary_in_atdd
    summary: drive design boundary-in from WHEN/THEN scenarios; boundary test fidelity chosen by risk; real-dependency confirmation where cheap
  - id: right_sizing_conscious
    summary: the smallest sufficient architecture is a recorded, bought-into choice, never a silent omission
  - id: persona_stance_attribution
    summary: hard choices attribute each persona stance as discourages/accepts/encourages; lead synthesises without forcing consensus
  - id: wiki_upkeep_warn_only
    summary: check-wiki is warn-only in project ready plus standalone; install-hooks is opt-in and non-blocking; the core check gate stays focused
  - id: unified_knowledge_graph
    summary: knowledge, specs, ADRs and wiki form one graph defined by TAXONOMY.md; edges must resolve

risks:
  - constrained TOON parsing in check-changes is a deliberate YAML subset, not a full parser
  - check-wiki staleness relies on git commit times and is skipped outside a git checkout
  - knowledge validation is lightweight Markdown frontmatter parsing

